Rhizophora stylosa

   [1851.jpg]
    Authority
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Rhizophorales:Rhizophoraceae
     Synonyms
   Common names mangrove, red mangrove, stilt mangrove, spider mangrove
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 1851

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A medium sized single- or multi-stemmed tree 8-30 m in height, while
   the trunk may reach a diameter of 25-60 cm. The tree has looping
   pneumatophores extending for several metres over the ground and aerial
   roots descending from the stem and branches. The crown is dark
   glossy-green and quit compact.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial.
   COMMON NAMES
   Small-stilted mangrove.
   FURTHER INF
   In Australia, the tree occurs naturally at sea level within the
   latitudinal range of 11-30Â°S. Small-stilted mangrove is common on beach
   fronts or lower tidal reaches and it may also extend upstream along
   tidal waterways that remain brackish for most of the year.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Boland D 1984 pp 610-611 [TEMP, KTMP, RAIN, USE]
   National RC 1980 pp 52-54 [DRA, SAL, TEXT, TEMP, KTMP, RAIN, DEP]

